// Man page for reset
manReset="RESET(8)                         X Shell Manual                         RESET(8)

<b>NAME</b>
    reset - clear X internal cache and shell cache
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>reset</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    <b>reset</b> is used to reset X internal cache and shell cache. Use this
    command when you have issues with dig or any other heavy shell command.
    Sometimes the cache can get corrupted and needs to be reset. This will clear
    all cached shell objects, network data, and internal state information.
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Basic Cache Reset</color>
    <b>reset</b>
    Clear all internal caches

    <color=#e4ff34># Common Use Cases</color>
    <b>reset</b>
    Fix dig command showing stale data

    <b>reset</b>
    Clear corrupted shell cache

    <b>reset</b>
    Resolve network query issues

    <b>reset</b>
    Refresh cached shell objects after system changes

    <b>reset</b>
    Fix memory or performance issues
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>reboot</b>, <b>dig</b>"